<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN269">
      <lg type="edition" style="pūṭṭuvil">
<l>kuyilvā yaṉṉa kūrmukai yatiral</l>
<l>payilā talkiya palkāḻ mālai</l>
<l>maiyirum pittai poliyac cūṭṭip</l>
<l>puttakaṟ koṇṭa pulikkaṇa veppa</l>
<l>roṉṟiru muṟaiyirun tuṇṭa piṉṟai</l>
<l>yuvalaik kaṇṇit tuṭiyaṉ vanteṉap</l>
<l>piḻimakiḻ valci vēṇṭa maṟṟitu</l>
<l>koḷḷā yeṉpa kaḷḷiṉ vāḻttik</l>
<l>karantai nīṭiya vaṟintumāṟu ceruviṟ</l>
<l>pallā ṉiṉanirai taḻīiya villōrk</l>
<l>koṭuñciṟaik kurūupparun tārppat</l>
<l>taṭintumāṟu peyarttatik karuṅkai vāḷē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The tiger-eyed keen men who had taken new bowls,</l>
<l>dashingly wearing in [their] kajal-dark hair tufts</l>
<l>garlands of many strands that stay without rattling</l>
<l>of the wild jasmine with buds as sharp as Koel beaks,</l>
<l>after sitting once [or] twice [and] eating</l>
<l>because the Tuṭi drummer with a leaf chaplet has come,</l>
<l>“if you want the pressed delight [and] food, take also </l>
<l>this”, they say, praising, like the toddy,</l>
<l>the sword in this black hand that has hewn down [and] removed opposition,</l>
<l>while the brilliant kites with bent wings cawed,</l>
<l>of those with bows who encompassed the herds of many cows</l>
<l>in a counter-fight, knowing the Karantai to be long.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
